	<title><%= params[:store] %> Store Reconciliation API</title>

	<body>

		<h1><%= params[:store] %> Store Reconciliation API</h1>
		
		<p>
		This is a demo implementation of a reconciliation API for the <%= params[:store] %>. The API is intended to 
		be used from the <a href="http://code.google.com/p/freebase-gridworks">Gridworks</a> application, allowing data loaded into the application to be linked to 
		resources in this store. 
		</p>
		
		<p>
		Note that this is a alpha quality API and is provided for exploration and feedback purposes. Discussion of the 
		general shape of the API should happen on the <a href="http://groups.google.com/group/freebase-gridworks/">gridworks list</a>. 
		Feedback on this particular implementation should be sent to myself.
		</p>
		
		<h2>API Console</h2>
		
		<p>Fill in a query below, to simulate a data item look-up</p>
		
		<form id="api-test" action="">
		<table>
		<tr>
			<td><label for="query">Query</label></td>
			<td><input type="text" id="query" name="query" value="Bath"></td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td><label for="limit">Limit</label></td>
			<td><input type="text" id="limit" name="limit" value="5"></td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td><label for="type">Type (URI)</label></td>
			<td><input type="text" id="type" name="type" value=""></td>		
		</tr>
			
		</table>
		<br />
		<input type="submit" id="submit" name="submit">
		 
		</form>
	
	
	<body>

</html>